A copy of the press release announcing the acquisition discussed under Item 8.01 below is furnished (not filed) as Exhibit 99.1 to this Current Report on Form 8-K and is incorporated by reference herein.
 
On December 21, 2007, Apogee Enterprises, Inc. announced that it had purchased 100 percent of the stock of Michigan-based Tubelite Inc., which fabricates aluminum storefront, entrance and curtainwall products for the U.S. commercial construction industry, for approximately $44 million (plus or minus closing adjustments).
 
