ERISA
(h) . (i) The Borrower or any Subsidiary, or any Person acting on behalf of the Borrower or a Subsidiary, or any Governmental Authority challenges the validity of any Loan Document or the Borrower's or a Subsidiary's obligations thereunder or any Loan Document ceases to be in full force and effect or is modified other than in accordance with the terms thereof and hereof, or (ii) any court or governmental or regulatory authority shall have enacted, issued, promulgated, enforced or entered any statute, rule, regulation, judgment, decree, injunction or other order (whether temporary, preliminary or permanent) which is in effect and which prohibits, enjoins or otherwise restricts, in a manner that, individually or in the aggregate, could reasonably be expected to have a Material Adverse Effect on any of the transactions contemplated under the Loan Documents.
Validity of Loan Documents
